  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "1 in a receding horizon manner from the current state to create a MPC feedback loop.",
    "Data Collection: We collected two datasets: one via teleoperation and another using Alg.",
    "1-first with ground-truth LiDAR for collision avoidance to train the initial collision model and subsequently using Alg.",
    "1 with the learned collision model to collect further refinement data.",
    "Data were recorded at 10 Hz, with each sample consisting of:• A standardized estimated point cloud of shape 300 × 2 obtained from Depth-Anything-V2 [1],• Robot state x = (x, y, ψ, v, ω), where (x, y) is position, ψ is heading, and v, ω are the linear and angular velocities (sampled uniformly from U[-1, 1] and clipped to [0, 1] m/s and [-1, 1] rad/s, respectively), • A control sequence u = (v, ω) where v, ω are the concatenation of the linear and angular velocities, respectively, at different timesteps, • Ground-truth clearance d gt from LiDAR (see IV-A)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
